'''Arvid Anseth''' (29 January 1925 – 3 August 2006) was a Norwegian ophthalmologist.

He was born in [[Bærum]]. He [[examen artium|finished]] his secondary education in 1943, took the [[Candidate of Medicine]] degree at [[Lund University]] in 1947 and the [[Doctor Medicinae (Danish and Norwegian degree)|Doctor Medicinae]] degree at Lund in 1961, after two years as a research fellow in [[Boston, MA|Boston]]. He was a [[docent]] at Lund University from 1962 to 1971, professor at the [[University of Tromsø]] from 197 to 1977, professor at the Faculty of Medicine, [[University of Trondheim|Trondheim]] from 1977 to 1980 and professor at the [[University of Oslo]]/[[Rikshospitalet]] from 1980 to 1989.<ref name=hvem>{{cite encyclopedia|year=1973|title=Anseth, Arvid|encyclopedia=[[Hvem er hvem?]]|editor=Steenstrup, Bjørn|publisher=Aschehoug|location=Oslo|url=http://runeberg.org/hvemerhvem/1973/0024.html|page=24|language=Norwegian|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=obit>{{cite news|title=Arvid Anseth|author=Hørven, Ivar|author2=Midelfart, Anna |author3=Opsahl, Roald |date=15 August 2006|page=Aftenposten|language=Norwegian}}</ref> Among others, he operated [[Olav V of Norway]] for a [[cataract]] in 1986.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kongen velbefinnende etter vellykket grå stær-operasjon|date=26 May 1986|language=Norwegian|agency=Norwegian News Agency}}</ref>

He was married, and resided in [[Larkollen]] in his later life.<ref>{{cite news|title=Han hjelper øyne til å se|author=Beck, Peter|date=29 January 1995|page=11|work=Aftenposten|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He died in August 2006.<ref name=obit/>

